  "(x - h)² + (y - k)² = r²": "",
  "Standard form of a linear equation is Ax + By = C, where A, B, and C are integers and A is typically non-negative. It is useful for finding intercepts and for systems of equations.": "",
  "What does it mean for two lines to be parallel?": "",
  "They intersect at exactly one point": "",
  "They have the same slope but different y-intercepts": "",
  "Their slopes are negative reciprocals": "",
  "They are the same line": "",
  "Two lines are parallel if and only if they have the same slope but different y-intercepts. Parallel lines never intersect — they maintain a constant distance apart.": "",
  "What does 'perpendicular' mean for two lines?": "",
  "They never intersect": "",
  "One is horizontal and the other has slope 1": "",
  "They intersect at a 90-degree angle and have slopes that are negative reciprocals": "",
  "They have the same slope": "",
  "Perpendicular lines meet at right angles (90°). Their slopes are negative reciprocals of each other: if one slope is m, the other is -1/m. For example, slopes of 2 and -1/2 are perpendicular.": "",
