  "A plumber charges a $50 service fee plus $30 per hour. If the total bill is modeled by C(h) = 30h + 50, how much does a 4-hour job cost?": "",
  "$170": "",
  "$200": "",
  "$120": "",
  "$80": "",
  "Substitute h = 4: C(4) = 30(4) + 50 = 120 + 50 = $170. The slope of 30 represents the hourly rate, and the y-intercept of 50 is the service fee.": "",
  "A candle is 12 inches tall and burns at a rate of 0.5 inches per hour. The height is modeled by h(t) = -0.5t + 12. After how many hours will the candle be completely burned?": "",
  "12 hours": "",
  "24 hours": "",
  "6 hours": "",
  "20 hours": "",
  "Set h(t) = 0: -0.5t + 12 = 0, so 0.5t = 12, giving t = 24 hours. The negative slope means the height decreases over time.": "",
  "A phone plan costs $0.10 per text plus a $20 monthly fee. If a customer sent 150 texts, what is the total monthly bill?": "",
  "$30": "",
  "$15": "",
  "$35": "",
  "Total = 0.10(150) + 20 = 15 + 20 = $35. The cost function is linear: C(t) = 0.10t + 20.": "",
  "Two hikers start at the same trailhead. Hiker A walks at 3 mph along a trail modeled by y = 3x. Hiker B starts 2 miles ahead and walks at 2 mph, modeled by y = 2x + 2. When will Hiker A catch Hiker B?": "",
